<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-449-648  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 449 648.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  May 1990 v111 n5 p14(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Laptops, palmtops - which computer are you buying? (includesrelated article on miniaturization in laptops)</TITLE><AUTHOR>O'Connor, Patrick J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Portable computers are getting smaller, since the first productwas introduced by Adam Osborne in the early 1980s.andP;  The 3.5-inchdisks made it possible to offer a hard drive for portables, suchas a Toshiba T3200 that offers 40Mbyte of memory, one Mbyte ofrandom access memory, and runs at 12MHz on an 80286 processor.andO;Portables are also growing more specialized, with proprietaryoperating systems and software, aimed at specific market niches.andO;The choice of portable depends upon the purpose.andP;  Hard drives areinherently unstable, especially in a machine which is bumped andmoved frequently.andP;  Battery life has always been a problem withportables, so manufacturers have concentrated on lessening powerdemands.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Portable computersLaptop ComputersMicrocomputers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>